<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. halidayi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="halidayi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">D. halidayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, and is close to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. caelebs" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="caelebs">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">D. caelebs</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by its smaller body size (only 1.1-1.2 mm), unobvious notauli, body coloration, median notch of distodorsal margin of gonostipes triangle and spatulated-shaped harpe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
